## WHAT HAS BEEN COMPLETED (DO NOT REDO)

### 1. District Database Expansion (location_data.py)
- **Expanded from 240 → 633 entries** covering all Indian states
- Added all major cities, wildlife sanctuaries, tiger reserves, national parks
- Added regional script entries (Hindi, Kannada, Tamil, Telugu, Bengali, Malayalam, Marathi, Gujarati, Punjabi, Odia)
- File: `app/utils/location_data.py` — fully rewritten and working

### 2. Startup Cleanup Enhancement (main.py)
- Function `_cleanup_existing_articles()` at line ~1366
- **Now searches BOTH title AND summary** for location matches (was title-only)
- Uses the expanded 633-entry district DB
- Applies 200+ regex post-filter to clean person names
- Cross-references persons against location DB to reject false positives
- Runs on every startup WITHOUT requiring AI model

### 3. Source Credibility Scoring (intelligence.py)
- Added `SOURCE_CREDIBILITY` dictionary at line ~179 with 40+ news sources rated 0.55–0.97
- Tier 1 (0.93–0.97): Mongabay, TRAFFIC, WWF, Down to Earth
- Tier 2 (0.88–0.92): The Hindu, Indian Express, NDTV, PTI, Reuters
- Tier 3 (0.80–0.87): Regional media (Deccan Herald, Prajavani, etc.)
- Tier 4 (0.55–0.70): Aggregators (LatestLY, NewsMeter)
- **Integrated into `analyze()` method** — confidence is nudged ±5% based on source reliability
- The `analyze()` method now accepts an optional `source: str = ""` parameter

### 4. Species-Aware Smuggling Route Intelligence (intelligence.py)
- Method `_likely_smuggling_route()` completely rewritten
- Now accepts `species: list[str] | None = None` parameter
- Contains **real TRAFFIC/WCCB-documented trafficking corridors**:
  - Tiger: MP→Rajasthan, Corbett→Delhi, Tadoba→Nagpur, Bandipur→ports
  - Red Sanders: Seshachalam→Chennai port→SE Asia
  - Pangolin: NE India→Myanmar, Odisha→Kolkata
  - Elephant: Kaziranga ivory routes, Kerala→Rajasthan carving hubs
- Falls back to geographic route logic (border/coastal/inland/NE corridor)
- Call site in `analyze()` updated to pass `species=species`

### 5. Entity-Aware Deduplication (dedupe.py)
- Method `_best_similarity_match()` enhanced with 3 new optional params: `species`, `involved_persons`, `published_at`
- **Entity boost**: When text similarity is borderline (≥0.70), shared persons add +0.07 each (max +0.15), shared species add +0.04 each (max +0.08)
- **Temporal decay**: Same-day matches get +0.03, 1-3 days +0.01, 10+ days -0.03
- New reason type: `"entity_match"` when entity overlap pushed score over threshold
- NOTE: The `find_duplicate()` method that calls `_best_similarity_match()` has NOT been updated to pass the new params yet — this needs to be done

### 6. Predictor Enhancements (predictor.py)
- **Seasonal Analysis** (`_compute_seasonal_analysis`): Monthly crime heatmap with Indian season markers (summer/monsoon/post_monsoon/winter), peak/low month detection, season aggregates
- **Smuggling Corridor Detection** (`_detect_smuggling_corridors`): Identifies state-species trafficking patterns from network-flagged articles with route keywords
- Both new methods added to training pipeline (steps 10 and 11)
- Both persisted in save/load model state
- Both exposed in `get_predictions()` API response

### 7. Previously Completed (before this session)
- 17 news provider adapters (Google, Bing, GDELT, DuckDuckGo, 11 Indian media RSS)
- 200+ entry person name post-filter (regex blocklist achieving 99.3% accuracy)
- Dual-mode AI (transformer + rule-based fallback for memory-constrained deployment)
- Excel auto-recovery for corrupted workbooks
- Professional README, CONTRIBUTING.md, SECURITY.md, GitHub templates
- 13-language search queries (Hindi, Kannada, Tamil, Telugu, Bengali, etc.)
- Admin authentication, audit logging, rate limiting
- React dashboard with KPI cards, Leaflet map, Recharts charts, incident table

